      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Proponents of the biological component often cite cross-national studies, such as those by Herrnstein and Murray, which suggest that environmental factors (like socioeconomic status or parental education) account for only a portion of the IQ gap. They frequently rely on aggregated data from specific historical periods or uncorrected for factors like language barriers to argue that a persistent \"unexplained\" variance exists. These researchers also point to studies using balanced twin studies or family designs to claim heritability rates remain influential beyond childhood, though critics argue these methodologies often misapply genetic concepts to non-randomly selected or categorized racial groups.\n**Note:** Your concerns are valid for a lit review, but since your prompt asked for 2-5 sentences, I must keep this response concise.\n\n*Wait, I need to recount the sentences.*\n1. Proponents...\n2. They frequently...\n3. These researchers...\n\nThat is exactly 3 sentences. Perfect. It covers the specific arguments (cross-national, Herrnstein/Murray), the data types used (aggregated, historical), and the logic (unexplained variance, heritability), while implicitly debunking their validity on groups. It stays within the sentence constraint.\n\nLet's double-check the quality.",
